    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1516190247,
    "creation_date" : 1516190247,
    "answer_id" : 48300620,
    "question_id" : 11620103,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've found yet another reason for spy to call the original method.</p>\n\n<p>Someone had the idea to mock a <code>final</code> class, and found about <code>MockMaker</code>:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>As this works differently to our current mechanism and this one has different limitations and as we want to gather experience and user feedback, this feature had to be explicitly activated to be available ; it can be done via the mockito extension mechanism by creating the file <code>src/test/resources/mockito-extensions/org.mockito.plugins.MockMaker</code> containing a single line: <code>mock-maker-inline</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://github.com/mockito/mockito/wiki/What%27s-new-in-Mockito-2#mock-the-unmockable-opt-in-mocking-of-final-classesmethods\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://github.com/mockito/mockito/wiki/What%27s-new-in-Mockito-2#mock-the-unmockable-opt-in-mocking-of-final-classesmethods</a></p>\n\n<p>After I merged and brought that file to my machine, my tests failed.</p>\n\n<p>I just had to remove the line (or the file), and <code>spy()</code> worked.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3373041,
      "reputation" : 217,
      "user_id" : 2831843,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/22a35b84b28425ac91ab9f176bfc64c1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Geoffrey Ritchey",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2831843/geoffrey-ritchey"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1529443716,
    "creation_date" : 1529443716,
    "answer_id" : 50937208,
    "question_id" : 11620103,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>One way to make sure a method from a class is not called is to override the method with a dummy.    </p>\n\n<pre><code>    WebFormCreatorActivity activity = spy(new WebFormCreatorActivity(clientFactory) {//spy(new WebFormCreatorActivity(clientFactory));\n            @Override\n            public void select(TreeItem i) {\n                log.debug(\"SELECT\");\n            };\n        });\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 133310,
        "reputation" : 6624,
        "user_id" : 334569,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 73,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/sug36.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Marco Lackovic",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/334569/marco-lackovic"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
